In our research, we utilize three datasets extensively employed in recommendation systems: Epinions1 11 11https://cseweb.ucsd.edu/ jmcauley/datasets.html Zhao et al. (2014), Zhao et al. (2014), KuaiRand2 22 22https://kuairand.com/ Gao et al. (2022) and Gao et al. (2022) and QB-video3 33 33https://static.qblv.qq.com/qblv/h5/algo-frontend/tenrec_dataset.html Yuan et al. (2022) each featuring different types of negative feedback. The characteristics of these datasets are detailed in Table Yuan et al. (2022) each featuring different types of negative feedback. The characteristics of these datasets are detailed in Table 1. To maintain dataset quality, we adhere to the commonly applied 10-core setting He et al. (2020) for preprocessing. He et al. Therefore, we consider the minor performance loss due to recommendation editing to be an acceptable trade-off.
